#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:3
#: c45029173239440fa171efc76c347e5c
msgid "Qubes Windows Tools (QWT)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:8
#: 75ca04be2bfd4a61b714ec2d462abd94
msgid ""
"As there is currently no officially supported version of Qubes Windows "
"Tools, the following instructions describe a workaround to get QWT "
"functionality using an old and a preliminary version of QWT.  When a new "
"officially supported version is made available, the following description"
" has to be updated accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:10
#: fb6d15c5c9754711b1212bc195714689
msgid ""
"Qubes Windows Tools (QWT) are a set of programs and drivers that provide "
"integration of Windows 7, 10, and 11 Standalone, TemplateVMs, and AppVMs "
"with the rest of the Qubes system. They contain several components that "
"can be enabled or disabled during installation and rely on specific "
"functions of Qubes, which support this integration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:12
#: 45a249a396234213805a1e9448909f55
msgid "**Shared components (required)** - common libraries used by QWT components"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:14
#: d7b23310216b4be8a3256b56e90ce6e2
msgid ""
"**Qubes GUI Agent** - video driver and GUI agent that enable the seamless"
" GUI mode that integrates Windows apps onto the common Qubes trusted "
"desktop (currently only for Windows 7 and, in a preliminary experimental "
"version, for Windows 10 and 11)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:16
#: f2079f8e38874f37a5cb3d0513d9b1d6
msgid ""
"**Disable UAC** - User Account Control may interfere with QWT and doesn't"
" really provide any additional benefits in Qubes environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:18
#: 427fe7ff1e2f438480c7842d40b2d50a
msgid ""
"**Clipboard sender/receiver** - Support for :doc:`secure clipboard "
"copy/paste </user/how-to-guides/how-to-copy-and-paste-text>` between the "
"Windows VM and other AppVMs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:20
#: 255d8b1003fb4d368cf6ea9e1d99c1e7
msgid ""
"**File sender/receiver** - Support for :doc:`secure file exchange </user"
"/how-to-guides/how-to-copy-and-move-files>` between the Windows VM and "
"other AppVMs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:22
#: ea51e0f05c3b4999a0f84a03f0f7340e
msgid ""
"**Xen PV drivers** - drivers for the virtual hardware exposed by Xen for "
"Windows that increase performance compared to QEMU emulated devices and "
"are required for attaching USB devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:24
#: ee723f16942447ad933a1e775b649e9d
msgid "Base Xen PV Drivers (required): paravirtual bus and interface drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:26
#: a67732a042d742fdaaf1476a61b81573
msgid "Xen PV Disk Drivers: paravirtual storage drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:28
#: 4944803e281648fe83cec32200509f2e
msgid "Xen PV Network Drivers: paravirtual network drivers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:30
#: dbe1b399f1534255b785414c3d1f68c8
msgid ""
"Move user profiles: user profile directory (``C:\\users``) is moved to "
"VM’s private disk backed by ``private.img file`` in ``dom0`` (useful "
"mainly for HVM templates)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:34
#: 88709cbd5c5e4fa393238a217832abb8
msgid ""
"**Qubes Core Agent** (part of Qubes) - Needed for proper integration with"
" Qubes as well as for ``qvm-run`` and generic ``qrexec`` for the Windows "
"VM (e.g., ability to run custom service within/from the Windows VM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:36
#: 8360e2ef2a414a7981bd0c8fba6ffab0
msgid ""
"**Copy/Edit in Disposable VM** (part of Qubes) - Support for editing "
"files in DisposableVMs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:38
#: 6c4a33a7684548f887338d4a09f09356
msgid ""
"**Audio** - Audio support is available even without QWT installation if "
"``qvm-features audio-model`` is set as ``ich6``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:43
#: 61056f3d83e34f19b314e7245c6ae001
msgid ""
"Due to the security problems described in `QSB-091 "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"secpack/blob/master/QSBs/qsb-091-2023.txt>`__, installation of Qubes "
"Windows Tools is currently blocked. Instead, a text file containing a "
"warning is displayed. Currently, it is difficult to estimate the severity"
" of the risks posed by the sources of the Xen drivers used in QWT "
"possibly being compromised, so it was decided not to offer direct QWT "
"installation until this problem could be treated properly. While Windows "
"qubes are, in Qubes, generally not regarded as being very trustworthy, a "
"possible compromise of the Xen drivers used in Qubes Windows Tools might "
"create a risk for Xen or `dom0` and thus be dangerous for Qubes itself. "
"This risk may be small or even non-existent, as stated in QSB-091. If you"
" **understand** this risk and are **willing to take it**, you can still "
"install the previous version of Qubes Windows Tools **for Windows 7**, "
"which will work for Windows 7, but not for Windows 10 or 11."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:45
#: 4c4a4a9e8b3a4dd89758db6546cb8cad
msgid ""
"**For Windows 10 or 11**, currently, there is no official, final QWT "
"version available, but for Qubes R4.3, a preliminary testing version has "
"been developed and can be used in Qubes R4.2. This version is not subject"
" to the security problems stated above, but it should be noted that it is"
" not yet in its final, debugged state and so may still show some errors. "
"The new Qubes graphics driver is not yet fully compatible with Windows "
"and should not be installed, as it may cause the Windows installation to "
"break and render it unusable. If the driver is installed despite these "
"risks and is working at least partially, switching to seamless mode and "
"staying there will probably work quite satisfactorily, but switching to "
"and from non-seamless mode is likely to cause trouble, as well as "
"changing the screen resolution will do there. So, usage of the new Qubes "
"graphics driver should be avoided unless a casual reboot of the Windows "
"VM is acceptable, even if it is partially working."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:48
#: 63c9de59746142ddb79411a8f2d5d312
msgid ""
"**Note**: If you choose to move profiles, drive letter ``Q:`` must be "
"assigned to the secondary (private) disk."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:50
#: 56dc6c6506ab43379b9ad90dba06f092
msgid ""
"**Note**: Xen PV disk drivers are not installed by default. This is "
"because they seem to cause problems (BSOD = Blue Screen Of Death). We're "
"working with upstream devs to fix this. **However**, the BSOD seems to "
"only occur after the first boot, and everything works fine after that. "
"**Enable the drivers at your own risk**, of course, but we welcome "
"reports of success/failure in any case (backup your VM first!). With disk"
" PV drivers absent, ``qvm-block`` will not work for the VM, but you can "
"still use standard Qubes inter-VM file copying mechanisms. On the other "
"hand, the Xen PV drivers allow USB device access even without QWT "
"installation if ``qvm-features stubdom-qrexec`` is set as ``1``."
msgstr ""

