#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:332
#: 87246e7722014b9e9928bd663968a92f
msgid "Xen PV drivers and Qubes Windows Tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:335
#: 91e6dc6f154849dc9537872683f6f523
msgid ""
"Installing Xen’s PV drivers in the VM will lower its resources usage when"
" using network and/or I/O intensive applications, but *may* come at the "
"price of system stability (although Xen’s PV drivers on a Windows VM are "
"usually very stable). They can be installed as an optional part of Qubes "
"Windows Tools (QWT), which bundles Xen’s PV drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:337
#: 683bb09542974d9c8ff6696eadc91c05
msgid "**Notes** about using Xen’s VBD (storage) PV driver:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:339
#: ec5e93a8110e42138fdaae19319afb15
msgid ""
"**Windows 7:** Installing the driver requires a fully updated VM, or else"
" you’ll likely get a BSOD (“Blue Screen Of Death”) and a VM in a "
"difficult-to-fix state. Updating Windows takes *hours* and for casual "
"usage there isn’t much of a performance between the disk PV driver and "
"the default one; so there is likely no need to go through the lengthy "
"Windows Update process if your VM doesn’t have access to untrusted "
"networks and if you don’t use I/O intensive apps or attach block devices."
" If you plan to update your newly installed Windows VM, it is recommended"
" that you do so *before* installing Qubes Windows Tools. Installing the "
"driver will probably cause Windows 7 activation to become invalid, but "
"the activation can be restored using the Microsoft telephone activation "
"method."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:341
#: 01d10705bdf947c9be4fd0bf51245dcb
msgid ""
"The option to install the storage PV driver is disabled by default in "
"Qubes Windows Tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:343
#: 55af0eacd5294ae1b612766b51751200
msgid ""
"In case you already had QWT installed without the storage PV driver and "
"you then updated the VM, you may then install the driver by again "
"starting the QWT installer and selecting the change option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:348
