#: 634c5bf7ea2c412aafca4a6a619140bc
msgid ""
"In the control panel, check again if the Xen drivers are removed. A Xen "
"Bus Package (version 8.2.1.8) may remain and cannot be removed, but does "
"no harm. Any other Xen drivers should have disappeared."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:653
#: 14d8b050bf254953bab2a52e83d7241c
msgid "Windows 10 and 11"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:656
#: 0285d978b0464ad69ca57c8fb0aede17
msgid ""
"If there is a drive ``D:`` from this earlier installation of Qubes "
"Windows Tools, it will probably contain incomplete private data; "
"especially the folder ``AppData`` containing program configuration data "
"will be missing. In this situation, it may be better to perform a new "
"Windows installation, because repair may be difficult and trouble-prone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:658
#: 0e99b2cb9b9c40f1b35a9e703b63d5d7
msgid ""
"First, be sure that the automatic repair function is disabled. In a "
"command window, execute ``bcdedit /set recoveryenabled NO``, and check "
"that this worked by issuing the command ``bcdedit``, without parameters, "
"again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:660
#: f19ed4286ed44d619dbf43c6749e19d4
msgid ""
"Now, uninstall QWT (currently version 4.2.1-1), using the Apps and "
"Features function of Windows. This will most likely result in a crash "
"with the error INACCESSIBLE BOOT DEVICE, especially if the PV drivers "
"were installed with QWT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:662
#: a79fcc9fae674e55a0f274c53eaac27a
msgid ""
"Restart Windows again, possibly two or three times, until repair options "
"are offered. By hitting the F8 key, select the restart menu, and there "
"select a start in safe mode (in German, it’s option number 4)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:664
#: f3a7715964af427a874a97f967766f13
msgid ""
"The system will start again, but in a rather useless way. Just shut it "
"down, and reboot again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:666
#: f12c1cdf39904a3ead4fc503f7487371
msgid ""
"Now Windows will start normally. Check in the Apps and Features display "
"if there are any Xen drivers left. If so, uninstall them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:670
#: c960aff36a0241fda61d7f12dc9b554a
msgid ""
"In the Apps and Features display, check again if the Xen drivers are "
"removed. A Xen Bus Package may remain and cannot be removed, but does no "
"harm. Any other Xen drivers should have disappeared."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:672
#: 521709f6296347df88b5bbe70a0833c1
msgid ""
"After successful uninstallation of the PV disk drivers, the disks will "
"appear as QEMU ATA disks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools.rst:674
#: c148b2d4c68f4badb7d7315fc2efe84a
msgid ""
"**Warning:** The uninstallation of the PV disk drivers may lead Windows "
"to declare that the hardware has changed and that, in consequence, the "
"activation is no longer valid, possibly complaining that the use of the "
"software is no longer lawful. It should be possible to reactivate the "
"software if a valid product key is provided."
msgstr ""

